com.github.lucbui.bytes

Class UnsignedByte

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.lucbui.bytes.UnsignedByte
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ByteObject<UnsignedByte>, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<UnsignedByte>

    public class UnsignedByte
extends java.lang.Object
implements ByteObject<UnsignedByte>, java.lang.Comparable<UnsignedByte>, java.io.Serializable
    Represents an Unsigned Byte. Unsigned bytes are immutable. Additionally, they are unique, so all UnsignedBytes of the same value are the same object.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
        Checks for equality with another UnsignedByte. UnsignedBytes are unique, so they can be compared with the == operator as well as this operator. If you want to compare two different UnsignedValues, use the equalsByValue operator.
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:
        obj - The object to compare to.
        Returns:
        True if the objects values are the same.

      • equalsByValue

        public boolean equalsByValue(java.lang.Object obj)
        Checks for equality amongst other Unsigned types. This allows equality checks between UnsignedByte and either UnsignedShort and UnsignedWord. Essentially, UnsignedByte.valueOf(0).equalsByValue(UnsignedShort.valueOf(0)) == true;
        Parameters:
        obj - The object to compare to.
        Returns:
        True if the objects values are the same
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassCastException - Obj cannot be cast to an UnsignedByte, UnsignedShort, or UnsignedWord.
